            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="306" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At a meeting of the United States, United Kingdom, and French Military Governors
                    for Germany at Frankfurt, November 4, General <persName corresp="#p_KGAP1">Koenig</persName> expressed his dissatisfaction over the plans for
                    international trusteeship for the Ruhr. For records of the meeting, see the
                    notes prepared by Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName> and
                    telegram 2686, November 5, from Berlin, <ref target="#pg_434">pages 434</ref>
                    and <ref target="#pg_438">438</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
